WEBVTT

00:00:37.095 --> 00:00:38.941
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

00:00:38.941 --> 00:00:40.795
- Hi, I'm Yook Jun Seo.
- Are you free next Friday?

00:00:40.795 --> 00:00:43.158
You're Lee Ui Yeong, right?

00:00:44.691 --> 00:00:46.951
Oh my gosh!

00:00:48.398 --> 00:00:50.714
Are you okay?

00:00:50.714 --> 00:00:52.048
Aren't you hurt?

00:00:52.048 --> 00:00:54.024
- Nice to meet you.
- I'm stationed in Gyodae.

00:00:54.024 --> 00:00:55.525
I'm calling about a blind date...

00:00:55.525 --> 00:00:59.589
Every single one of these
is a blind date request?

00:01:00.743 --> 00:01:01.870
What's going on?

00:01:01.870 --> 00:01:03.897
That's what I'd like to know.

00:01:03.897 --> 00:01:05.770
Sorry?

00:01:06.541 --> 00:01:09.759
[Episode 3]

00:01:12.386 --> 00:01:13.873
Did I get hacked?

00:01:13.873 --> 00:01:14.940
Was my number leaked?

00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:15.981
My phone carrier issue?

00:01:15.981 --> 00:01:18.565
No, the shopping site?

00:01:19.471 --> 00:01:21.112
- Hello, nice to meet you.
- Who is this?

00:01:21.112 --> 00:01:23.245
This is Yoon Bak.

00:01:24.184 --> 00:01:25.668
My name is Yook Jun Seo.

00:01:25.668 --> 00:01:28.465
I'm Lee Ho Kwang, I sing and act on stage.

00:01:28.465 --> 00:01:30.051
When are you free this week?

00:01:30.051 --> 00:01:31.191
Hello, Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:01:31.191 --> 00:01:33.894
I'm Kim Do Yoon, your dermatologist's brother.

00:01:33.894 --> 00:01:34.903
What's going on?

00:01:34.903 --> 00:01:37.482
Hello, I'm Song Ji Hoon. Na Hyun's friend.

00:01:37.482 --> 00:01:39.528
I showed him your picture
and he wants to meet you.

00:01:39.528 --> 00:01:41.272
He teaches kids and he's popular.

00:01:41.272 --> 00:01:43.725
- I'll give him your number.
- Wait a second.

00:01:43.725 --> 00:01:44.997
Let me check and I'll get back to you.

00:01:44.997 --> 00:01:46.373
I gave your number to my friend.

00:01:46.373 --> 00:01:47.925
- Out of nowhere?
- I'll pass your number to him.

00:01:47.925 --> 00:01:50.625
Okay, I'll look into it.

00:01:56.591 --> 00:01:58.321
[Set me up on a blind date.]

00:02:00.011 --> 00:02:01.985
[Hey, find me a good guy.]

00:02:04.421 --> 00:02:05.547
[Paste]

00:02:05.547 --> 00:02:07.479
[Don't you have any single guy friends?]

00:02:07.479 --> 00:02:09.419
[Please set me up.]

00:02:11.377 --> 00:02:13.410
Oh my.

00:02:14.199 --> 00:02:17.484
I can't believe I did that.

00:02:18.363 --> 00:02:20.866
I'm insane!

00:02:24.679 --> 00:02:27.445
- I'm home.
- Yeah.

00:02:28.433 --> 00:02:30.924
- Oh my goodness.
- My shoulders hurt.

00:02:30.924 --> 00:02:32.418
Hey.

00:02:32.418 --> 00:02:34.304
Yeah?

00:02:35.337 --> 00:02:37.697
What is all this?

00:02:37.697 --> 00:02:41.371
You were so excited
about wearing a hotel uniform.

00:02:41.371 --> 00:02:43.777
Are you sick?

00:02:44.592 --> 00:02:46.387
- You don't have a fever...
- Come on.

00:02:46.387 --> 00:02:47.846
Mom, that's not it.

00:02:47.846 --> 00:02:49.136
From now on, when I come home drunk,

00:02:49.136 --> 00:02:51.161
turn off my phone for me.
Or just cut off my wrist.

00:02:51.161 --> 00:02:53.162
Shouldn't we cut up your credit card instead?

00:02:53.162 --> 00:02:54.703
This isn't just clothes.

00:02:54.703 --> 00:02:56.073
It's armor.

00:02:56.073 --> 00:02:57.664
Look.

00:02:57.664 --> 00:02:58.904
What kind of armor

00:02:58.904 --> 00:03:02.287
is this soft and fluffy?

00:03:02.287 --> 00:03:04.951
Then what about this?

00:03:04.951 --> 00:03:07.358
Is this camouflage cream?

00:03:07.358 --> 00:03:08.936
Oh my gosh.

00:03:08.936 --> 00:03:10.500
Don't even think about using it.

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:13.284
Just don't touch anything else.

00:03:17.805 --> 00:03:19.615
If it hides your flaws

00:03:19.615 --> 00:03:21.395
and boosts your confidence,

00:03:21.395 --> 00:03:23.601
that's armor.

00:03:26.556 --> 00:03:28.616
Okay.

00:03:39.110 --> 00:03:41.375
It may have started as drunk texting,

00:03:41.375 --> 00:03:44.376
but an opportunity is still an opportunity.

00:03:47.279 --> 00:03:49.977
Even if it's just a one-percent chance.

00:03:49.977 --> 00:03:54.023
I just need to meet them and
find someone who's right for me.

00:03:55.655 --> 00:03:57.054
I'll look into it.

00:03:57.054 --> 00:03:59.447
Ui Yeong, I can smell the alcohol from here.

00:03:59.447 --> 00:04:00.985
- Let's grab a meal sometime.
- All of a sudden?

00:04:00.985 --> 00:04:02.518
- I'll see what I can do.
- Are you drunk?

00:04:02.518 --> 00:04:04.052
If I had someone to set you up with,
I would've dated him myself.

00:04:04.052 --> 00:04:06.557
They're just empty words...

00:04:06.557 --> 00:04:07.754
I'll look into it.

00:04:07.754 --> 00:04:09.347
But I have a favor, too.

00:04:09.347 --> 00:04:12.007
Can you book a wedding hall consultation
at your hotel for me?

00:04:12.007 --> 00:04:15.133
Yeah, it's all about give and take.

00:04:15.133 --> 00:04:16.377
Sure.

00:04:16.377 --> 00:04:19.651
So when works for you?

00:04:19.651 --> 00:04:21.454
[Hello, nice to meet you. This is Yoon Bak.]

00:04:21.454 --> 00:04:23.911
Hello, this is Lee Ui Yeong.

00:04:23.911 --> 00:04:26.811
How about this Saturday?

00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:28.948
Nice.

00:04:28.948 --> 00:04:30.441
[1:30 PM / Yoon Bak / 37]

00:04:30.441 --> 00:04:32.159
[Math Instructor]

00:04:32.159 --> 00:04:33.207
[Save]

00:04:33.207 --> 00:04:35.182
[1:30 PM / Yoon Bak / 37]

00:04:38.771 --> 00:04:41.885
Morning, Ui Yeong.

00:04:41.885 --> 00:04:44.608
Oh, is one of those for me?

00:04:44.608 --> 00:04:45.927
No, they're both mine.

00:04:45.927 --> 00:04:48.072
I need both of these to wake up.

00:04:48.072 --> 00:04:50.401
What? Didn't sleep?

00:04:50.401 --> 00:04:52.748
You look pretty, though.

00:04:53.361 --> 00:04:56.035
Why's your schedule so packed?

00:04:56.035 --> 00:04:59.824
Wait... these are blind dates?

00:05:02.068 --> 00:05:03.708
[7:30 AM / Lee Sung Jae / 31 / Designer]

00:05:03.708 --> 00:05:06.122
Who goes on a blind date before work?

00:05:06.122 --> 00:05:08.366
Yeah. That would be me.

00:05:08.366 --> 00:05:12.192
I didn't really have a choice.
I don't have time.

00:05:12.192 --> 00:05:13.922
Yesterday I was just

00:05:13.922 --> 00:05:16.022
trying to clean up the mess I made...

00:05:16.022 --> 00:05:17.552
but this isn't right, is it?

00:05:17.552 --> 00:05:19.149
It's hard enough meeting one person.

00:05:19.149 --> 00:05:20.787
And this feels kind of rude, right?

00:05:20.787 --> 00:05:21.888
Well,

00:05:21.888 --> 00:05:23.792
you're not in a relationship with any of them.

00:05:23.792 --> 00:05:25.690
As long as you give it your best each time,

00:05:25.690 --> 00:05:27.735
you've done your part.

00:05:27.735 --> 00:05:30.036
Come on, just go for it.

00:05:30.036 --> 00:05:31.356
And more importantly,

00:05:31.356 --> 00:05:34.102
if you cancel now,

00:05:34.102 --> 00:05:35.420
the blind dates will dry up.

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:38.380
You'll lose your matchmakers for good.

00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:42.266
That can't happen.

00:05:47.739 --> 00:05:48.824
[The premium whisky brand]

00:05:48.824 --> 00:05:50.176
Starting mid-next month,

00:05:50.176 --> 00:05:52.455
our hotel will be hosting

00:05:52.455 --> 00:05:54.226
the 100th anniversary event

00:05:54.226 --> 00:05:55.914
for the premium whisky brand Deerfiddich.

00:05:55.914 --> 00:05:58.425
- Oh.
- Wow.

00:05:58.425 --> 00:06:00.487
This big project lands right
when I'm swamped...

00:06:00.487 --> 00:06:01.933
The event runs for three weeks?

00:06:01.933 --> 00:06:05.299
Yes. We're planning a whisky exhibition

00:06:05.299 --> 00:06:07.803
and tasting event as a pop-up
in the hotel lobby.

00:06:07.803 --> 00:06:08.948
The brand has entrusted us

00:06:08.948 --> 00:06:12.643
with the overall planning and operations.

00:06:13.917 --> 00:06:15.175
If that's the concept,

00:06:15.175 --> 00:06:18.721
what if we build temporary walls
and create more of a shop-in-shop feel?

00:06:18.721 --> 00:06:20.885
Put up proper signage, bring in a bartender,

00:06:20.885 --> 00:06:22.785
and recreate a whisky bar
you'd find in Scotland

00:06:22.785 --> 00:06:24.776
right in the hotel lobby.

00:06:24.776 --> 00:06:25.929
That sounds great.

00:06:25.929 --> 00:06:27.843
Let's develop it in that direction.

00:06:27.843 --> 00:06:28.916
Purchasing Team,

00:06:28.916 --> 00:06:31.085
please find a vendor that can handle
the spatial design and setup.

00:06:31.085 --> 00:06:32.475
- Got it.
- And Facilities Team,

00:06:32.475 --> 00:06:34.268
we'll need your support
during on-site construction.

00:06:34.268 --> 00:06:36.566
Say no more. We'll take care of it.

00:06:36.566 --> 00:06:39.478
So... do we get a free drink out of this?

00:06:54.201 --> 00:06:56.541
I'm counting on you.

00:06:58.726 --> 00:07:01.239
[Purchasing Team]

00:07:09.600 --> 00:07:12.531
Ui Yeong has worked nonstop this whole time.

00:07:12.531 --> 00:07:15.121
Any time there was a problem,
she showed up and fixed it. Right?

00:07:15.121 --> 00:07:16.193
Yeah.

00:07:16.193 --> 00:07:18.877
Let's let her focus on
her own life for a while.

00:07:18.877 --> 00:07:20.901
We'll put what we've learned to use.

00:07:20.901 --> 00:07:23.471
You've got to prove yourself
before your internship ends, right?

00:07:23.471 --> 00:07:26.464
Yes. I'll really give it my all.

00:07:26.464 --> 00:07:28.531
Good.

00:07:29.141 --> 00:07:31.107
- Drink up.
- Thank you.

00:07:32.635 --> 00:07:35.478
[Attorney Kang Do Hyun]
Sae Byeok, are you free tonight?

00:07:35.478 --> 00:07:37.757
- Let's talk for a minute.
- All right.

00:07:37.757 --> 00:07:39.868
Want to grab dinner
and then start looking up vendors?

00:07:39.868 --> 00:07:42.434
- Yes.
- Cheers.

00:07:55.224 --> 00:07:57.324
You look great.

00:08:00.655 --> 00:08:02.848
That looks delicious.

00:08:05.413 --> 00:08:07.320
Hello.

00:08:11.384 --> 00:08:13.575
What I realized
from going on blind dates was this.

00:08:13.575 --> 00:08:15.035
The world is big,

00:08:15.035 --> 00:08:17.135
and there are
so many different kinds of people.

00:08:17.135 --> 00:08:20.164
Not a single one was the same...

00:08:20.164 --> 00:08:22.459
not even similar.

00:08:22.459 --> 00:08:24.550
Each person was completely unique.

00:08:24.550 --> 00:08:26.927
- Each one was a universe.
- Hello, it's nice to meet you.

00:08:26.927 --> 00:08:28.137
You recognize me, right?

00:08:28.137 --> 00:08:29.407
I'm Yoon Bak.

00:08:29.407 --> 00:08:32.962
[Yoon Bak, 37, Star Math Instructor]

00:08:38.532 --> 00:08:39.936
You're done already?

00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:41.689
Would you like another soup?

00:08:41.689 --> 00:08:43.252
Already taking care of me?

00:08:43.252 --> 00:08:45.136
That's some serious flirting.

00:08:45.136 --> 00:08:46.227
Sorry?

00:08:46.227 --> 00:08:47.480
I'm kidding.

00:08:47.480 --> 00:08:49.430
I usually eat while meeting
with other instructors,

00:08:49.430 --> 00:08:51.137
so I'm used to eating fast.

00:08:52.693 --> 00:08:54.097
I see.

00:08:54.097 --> 00:08:55.548
You must be really busy.

00:08:55.548 --> 00:08:58.067
I heard your classes are extremely popular.

00:08:58.067 --> 00:09:00.091
Is that what you're really curious about?

00:09:00.091 --> 00:09:01.099
Or is it more like,

00:09:01.099 --> 00:09:02.499
"Are you too busy to date?"

00:09:02.499 --> 00:09:04.257
"Can you care about me,
not just your students?"

00:09:04.257 --> 00:09:06.277
Well...

00:09:07.764 --> 00:09:09.807
Is your schedule okay for meeting me?

00:09:09.807 --> 00:09:11.414
Time is money to me.

00:09:11.414 --> 00:09:13.604
But for you,
maybe it's silver... or even bronze.

00:09:13.604 --> 00:09:14.848
And yet here we are,

00:09:14.848 --> 00:09:16.181
focusing on each other.

00:09:16.181 --> 00:09:19.701
If these interactions keep building up,
what do you think happens?

00:09:20.824 --> 00:09:22.181
What do you think happens?

00:09:22.181 --> 00:09:23.428
Well...

00:09:23.428 --> 00:09:25.943
The ending's obvious.

00:09:25.943 --> 00:09:27.742
You've passed as my girlfriend.

00:09:27.742 --> 00:09:28.418
Sorry?

00:09:28.418 --> 00:09:30.739
If you want dating, I'll take it there.

00:09:30.739 --> 00:09:32.802
If you want marriage, I'll take it there.

00:09:32.802 --> 00:09:34.369
So don't overthink it.

00:09:34.369 --> 00:09:35.733
Just use me.

00:09:35.733 --> 00:09:36.859
It's okay.

00:09:36.859 --> 00:09:38.589
Any questions?

00:09:38.589 --> 00:09:39.779
A man who flirts

00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:41.990
like he's lecturing a room full of seniors.

00:09:41.990 --> 00:09:44.607
I heard you're really into working out.

00:09:44.607 --> 00:09:46.091
Are carbs okay?

00:09:46.091 --> 00:09:47.618
Yeah, I exercise,

00:09:47.618 --> 00:09:49.464
so I actually prefer eating a lot.

00:09:49.464 --> 00:09:52.004
[Yook Jun Seo, 29, Rehab Trainer, Former UDT]

00:09:53.957 --> 00:09:57.294
What matters most to you in a relationship?

00:09:57.294 --> 00:09:58.431
Food.

00:09:58.431 --> 00:10:00.278
If our appetites don't match,

00:10:00.278 --> 00:10:02.302
you feel that every time you eat together.

00:10:02.302 --> 00:10:04.454
What about you? Do you eat well?

00:10:04.454 --> 00:10:08.367
Yeah, I love food. I'm not picky at all.

00:10:08.367 --> 00:10:10.800
I've got tons of restaurants saved on my map.

00:10:10.800 --> 00:10:13.464
Since we're talking about it,
we could hit a few spots today.

00:10:13.464 --> 00:10:15.678
I'm getting excited already.

00:10:15.678 --> 00:10:18.411
- A few?
- Yeah.

00:10:21.859 --> 00:10:24.013
Tacos!

00:10:32.982 --> 00:10:35.184
Bagels!

00:10:35.184 --> 00:10:37.284
Gelato!

00:10:38.812 --> 00:10:40.912
Dessert!

00:10:47.890 --> 00:10:49.549
A second date with him

00:10:49.549 --> 00:10:52.762
might send my stomach into shock.

00:11:01.520 --> 00:11:04.222
Well... I was going to get the coffee today...

00:11:04.222 --> 00:11:07.595
♪ Don't say that ♪

00:11:07.595 --> 00:11:10.071
[Lee Ho Kwang, 36, Musical Actor]

00:11:10.733 --> 00:11:13.590
Today, you've given me

00:11:13.590 --> 00:11:15.911
a perfect day beyond price.

00:11:15.911 --> 00:11:18.732
From now on,

00:11:18.732 --> 00:11:21.504
you are my muse.

00:11:21.504 --> 00:11:22.615
Your... muse?

00:11:22.615 --> 00:11:24.385
Like Christine...

00:11:24.385 --> 00:11:26.418
to the Phantom.

00:11:26.418 --> 00:11:28.431
The Phantom?

00:11:29.118 --> 00:11:30.208
Mr. Ho Kwang,

00:11:30.208 --> 00:11:31.595
it's getting late,

00:11:31.595 --> 00:11:33.112
so I should head out.

00:11:33.112 --> 00:11:34.999
My place is right here. I'll go on my own.

00:11:34.999 --> 00:11:38.359
♪ No ♪

00:11:38.359 --> 00:11:41.259
I won't feel at ease unless I see you home.

00:11:41.259 --> 00:11:43.506
I can sense

00:11:43.506 --> 00:11:45.465
the dark intentions of men
circling my sunshine.

00:11:45.465 --> 00:11:47.864
The man who called me Muse, Christine,

00:11:47.864 --> 00:11:49.423
and Sunshine...

00:11:49.423 --> 00:11:50.768
and tried to overprotect me.

00:11:50.768 --> 00:11:52.047
You should probably go.

00:11:52.047 --> 00:11:54.671
Seems like she doesn't want to
share her address.

00:11:54.671 --> 00:11:56.042
Who are you, lady?

00:11:56.042 --> 00:11:59.007
Why are you interfering between us like this?

00:11:59.007 --> 00:12:00.847
Me? I'm her mother.

00:12:00.847 --> 00:12:02.578
Jesus Christ...

00:12:02.578 --> 00:12:04.084
Superstar.

00:12:04.084 --> 00:12:06.448
Not superstar. Her mother.

00:12:06.448 --> 00:12:08.274
You really don't listen, do you?

00:12:08.274 --> 00:12:10.004
And sometimes,
after meeting my greatest rival in love,

00:12:10.004 --> 00:12:11.654
things ended in total disaster.

00:12:11.654 --> 00:12:13.764
♪ Mother ♪

00:12:13.764 --> 00:12:15.208
♪ My mother... ♪

00:12:15.208 --> 00:12:18.154
♪ Your mother ♪

00:12:26.044 --> 00:12:28.655
Let us offer a prayer of gratitude
to Almighty God the Father

00:12:28.655 --> 00:12:30.899
who brought us together.

00:12:30.899 --> 00:12:32.676
[Prayer Guy, 32]
The guy who says Sunday is the Lord's Day

00:12:32.676 --> 00:12:34.079
so even dating takes the day off.

00:12:34.079 --> 00:12:35.484
Do you like drinking too?

00:12:35.484 --> 00:12:37.082
You could just drink alone at home.

00:12:37.082 --> 00:12:39.079
Why go out of your way to drink outside?

00:12:39.079 --> 00:12:40.736
[Breakup Guy, 30]
A man who clearly isn't over

00:12:40.736 --> 00:12:43.055
his ex-girlfriend yet.

00:12:43.055 --> 00:12:45.120
It's fine if we have different tastes.

00:12:45.120 --> 00:12:46.378
But what bothers me is...

00:12:46.378 --> 00:12:48.326
Why pour the sauce without even asking?

00:12:48.326 --> 00:12:50.142
I think that says a lot about you.

00:12:50.142 --> 00:12:51.933
[Sauce Guy, 35]
A dip-it guy who can't tolerate

00:12:51.933 --> 00:12:53.662
the recklessness of a pour-it-all-over girl.

00:12:53.662 --> 00:12:55.486
- Please go out with me.
- Please go out with me.

00:12:55.486 --> 00:12:56.950
- Please see me.
- Please meet me.

00:12:56.950 --> 00:12:58.049
Date me.

00:12:58.049 --> 00:13:00.875
The problem was, out of all those men,

00:13:00.875 --> 00:13:04.107
not one of them was my type.

00:13:20.539 --> 00:13:23.003
Ms. Ui Yeong!

00:13:23.003 --> 00:13:24.287
Please go out with me.

00:13:24.287 --> 00:13:26.467
Ms. Ui Yeong, wait.

00:13:26.467 --> 00:13:28.124
I love you!

00:13:28.124 --> 00:13:30.148
Stop right there!

00:13:30.148 --> 00:13:31.525
- Ms. Ui Yeong!
- Ms. Ui Yeong!

00:13:31.525 --> 00:13:33.545
Ms. Ui Yeong!

00:13:46.563 --> 00:13:48.510
When I said you passed, that meant I liked you.

00:13:48.510 --> 00:13:50.346
Let's go somewhere even better
to eat next time.

00:13:50.346 --> 00:13:53.224
Your mother has incredible charisma...

00:13:53.224 --> 00:13:54.794
[Lee Eun Mi]
We're heading to the hotel now.

00:13:54.794 --> 00:13:56.352
See you soon.

00:13:56.352 --> 00:13:58.855
Oh no, I'm late.

00:14:11.487 --> 00:14:13.413
Mr. Tae Seop.

00:14:18.054 --> 00:14:20.033
Mr. Tae Seop.

00:14:28.874 --> 00:14:30.848
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:39.174
You said you'd call...

00:14:39.174 --> 00:14:42.353
Don't tell me things worked out with that guy.

00:14:44.183 --> 00:14:47.149
[Director of Animal House]

00:14:50.715 --> 00:14:53.014
Hello?

00:14:53.014 --> 00:14:54.952
Hey, you're actually getting married.

00:14:54.952 --> 00:14:56.042
Congratulations.

00:14:56.042 --> 00:14:57.337
Thank you so much.

00:14:57.337 --> 00:14:59.331
It's nice having a friend who works at a hotel.

00:14:59.331 --> 00:15:00.374
It's really no big deal.

00:15:00.374 --> 00:15:03.646
Just so you know,
weekend consultations are fully booked.

00:15:03.646 --> 00:15:06.073
I'm squeezing you in as a special favor,

00:15:06.073 --> 00:15:08.639
so... don't go telling everyone, okay?

00:15:08.639 --> 00:15:09.991
Don't worry.

00:15:09.991 --> 00:15:14.036
Who else could afford a luxury hotel like this?

00:15:14.849 --> 00:15:18.110
By the way,
you two have totally different styles.

00:15:18.110 --> 00:15:19.711
We're different, but we work.

00:15:19.711 --> 00:15:22.202
Back in college,
we were on a group project together.

00:15:22.202 --> 00:15:25.044
Back then, she handled
all the work and presentations,

00:15:25.044 --> 00:15:28.024
and I just sent her 100,000 won.

00:15:28.024 --> 00:15:29.749
- And the result?
- An A-plus.

00:15:30.825 --> 00:15:34.637
There's no one who trusted me more
and delivered like you did.

00:15:34.637 --> 00:15:38.484
With all that competence,
how are you still single?

00:15:38.484 --> 00:15:39.509
- Baby.
- Yeah?

00:15:39.509 --> 00:15:40.729
Don't you have anyone

00:15:40.729 --> 00:15:43.668
you could introduce her to?

00:15:43.668 --> 00:15:44.692
You didn't even look?

00:15:44.692 --> 00:15:46.682
I told you to check.

00:15:46.682 --> 00:15:48.492
Hey, don't do that.
You're making him uncomfortable.

00:15:48.492 --> 00:15:50.393
It's fine. I'm okay.

00:15:50.393 --> 00:15:51.592
You're so clueless.

00:15:51.592 --> 00:15:53.102
Ms. Lee Eun Mi, our bride-to-be.

00:15:53.102 --> 00:15:54.909
Oh, General Manager.

00:15:54.909 --> 00:15:57.732
I'm Eun Jeong Seok,
General Manager of The Hills.

00:15:57.732 --> 00:15:58.975
Let's move to the banquet hall,

00:15:58.975 --> 00:16:01.102
where I'll introduce you
to our wedding manager.

00:16:01.102 --> 00:16:02.379
You can leave the rest to me.

00:16:02.379 --> 00:16:03.552
Please take good care of her.

00:16:03.552 --> 00:16:06.138
We'll make sure everything is perfect.

00:16:07.573 --> 00:16:09.712
I'll see you later.

00:16:11.259 --> 00:16:13.733
Ui Yeong.

00:16:13.733 --> 00:16:15.833
Why are you here?

00:16:17.913 --> 00:16:19.837
So... you were staying here,

00:16:19.837 --> 00:16:21.442
checking out,

00:16:21.442 --> 00:16:23.806
and ran into the General Manager?

00:16:23.806 --> 00:16:25.999
What if people start talking?

00:16:25.999 --> 00:16:28.792
Hey, the employee discount is sacred.

00:16:28.792 --> 00:16:29.714
And besides,

00:16:29.714 --> 00:16:32.383
if word gets around that
two consenting adults had sex,

00:16:32.383 --> 00:16:34.485
that's the ridiculous part, yeah?

00:16:34.485 --> 00:16:36.819
Beats me.

00:16:38.029 --> 00:16:38.973
But honestly,

00:16:38.973 --> 00:16:42.938
meeting people just isn't fun these days.

00:16:42.938 --> 00:16:44.735
It's always the same pattern.

00:16:44.735 --> 00:16:46.312
You meet, exchange names,

00:16:46.312 --> 00:16:47.705
eat, sleep together, and that's it.

00:16:47.705 --> 00:16:49.183
I can't see them a second time.

00:16:49.183 --> 00:16:51.629
Maybe I need a new obsession or something.

00:16:51.629 --> 00:16:54.402
I kind of see what you mean.

00:16:58.651 --> 00:17:02.250
When I said you passed, that meant I liked you.

00:17:03.797 --> 00:17:06.817
And when I said you could use me,
that was a sign of interest too.

00:17:06.817 --> 00:17:08.011
But

00:17:08.011 --> 00:17:09.295
if you keep seeing them,

00:17:09.295 --> 00:17:11.362
wouldn't feelings start to grow?

00:17:11.362 --> 00:17:14.561
They're all decent, accomplished guys.

00:17:14.561 --> 00:17:16.564
How long are you supposed to wait?

00:17:16.564 --> 00:17:19.024
Hey, if they're decent,
don't string them along.

00:17:19.024 --> 00:17:21.457
Let them find someone who's right for them.

00:17:21.457 --> 00:17:23.934
If it's not working for you, saying no is

00:17:23.934 --> 00:17:27.167
the polite thing to do in the blind date. Okay?

00:17:33.743 --> 00:17:35.160
I'm sorry.

00:17:35.160 --> 00:17:37.453
I don't think we're the right match.

00:17:37.453 --> 00:17:40.510
I hope you meet someone great.

00:17:45.180 --> 00:17:47.425
Your mother has incredible charisma.

00:17:47.425 --> 00:17:50.622
Outside your home, I could be your umbrella.

00:17:50.622 --> 00:17:52.482
Though on a sunny day like this,
you wouldn't need one.

00:17:52.482 --> 00:17:54.186
I suppose this is where our story ends.

00:17:54.186 --> 00:17:56.896
♪ The end ♪

00:17:56.896 --> 00:18:00.126
If you can end things, you can get ended too.

00:18:00.126 --> 00:18:03.086
That's just how blind dates are.

00:18:06.203 --> 00:18:08.023
You're right.

00:18:22.396 --> 00:18:24.996
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:18:24.996 --> 00:18:27.006
Hey, you've been good?

00:18:27.006 --> 00:18:29.123
Don't fight.

00:18:29.123 --> 00:18:31.209
Seoltang!

00:18:31.209 --> 00:18:33.019
Hello.

00:18:33.019 --> 00:18:35.907
Thanks for coming on such short notice.

00:18:35.907 --> 00:18:38.923
Seoltang even got a nice bath.

00:18:38.923 --> 00:18:40.344
You look so pretty.

00:18:40.344 --> 00:18:43.307
Be happy and loved in your new home,

00:18:43.307 --> 00:18:45.200
okay?

00:18:46.363 --> 00:18:48.759
Yes, thank you.

00:18:52.270 --> 00:18:55.156
[80, Geumyeonghwa 22-gil, Paju-si, Gyeonggi-do]

00:18:55.156 --> 00:18:57.040
We'd like to cancel the adoption.

00:18:57.040 --> 00:18:58.433
May I ask why?

00:18:58.433 --> 00:19:00.900
I'm sure this wasn't a snap decision.

00:19:00.900 --> 00:19:02.310
In the photos,

00:19:02.310 --> 00:19:04.227
she looked like the dog I used to have,

00:19:04.227 --> 00:19:05.560
so I felt attached.

00:19:05.560 --> 00:19:07.679
But in person, she's kind of different.

00:19:07.679 --> 00:19:09.710
Bigger than I expected.
And her fur's not that great.

00:19:09.710 --> 00:19:12.360
Was it raised outside?
It's not carrying any diseases, is it?

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:14.030
Watch what you say.

00:19:14.030 --> 00:19:17.257
It's not like animals understand us anyway.

00:19:17.257 --> 00:19:20.020
They do.

00:19:20.020 --> 00:19:21.937
They can tell from our faces and our tone

00:19:21.937 --> 00:19:23.574
whether we're happy or upset,

00:19:23.574 --> 00:19:25.898
whether we like them or not.

00:19:25.898 --> 00:19:27.415
Someday,

00:19:27.415 --> 00:19:28.934
I hope you go through
what Seoltang went through today

00:19:28.934 --> 00:19:30.561
and feel that heartbreak yourselves.

00:19:30.561 --> 00:19:33.277
Because I don't think you'll ever understand
until you do.

00:19:33.277 --> 00:19:35.737
- What did you say?
- Let's go.

00:19:35.737 --> 00:19:36.987
Hey. Let go.

00:19:36.987 --> 00:19:38.654
What did you say?

00:19:38.654 --> 00:19:40.567
Say that again.

00:19:48.147 --> 00:19:50.370
Where are you?

00:19:54.967 --> 00:19:58.707
- Please don't run.
- Yes.

00:19:58.707 --> 00:20:00.544
He's a scammer.

00:20:00.544 --> 00:20:02.554
Wait.

00:20:02.554 --> 00:20:05.365
Mr. Song, are you okay?

00:20:05.365 --> 00:20:07.151
What's going on?

00:20:07.151 --> 00:20:08.675
You young people!

00:20:08.675 --> 00:20:10.937
A dog isn't a toy!

00:20:10.937 --> 00:20:13.534
Adopting a pet should be done carefully!

00:20:13.534 --> 00:20:14.940
And responsibly!

00:20:14.940 --> 00:20:16.514
What kind of crap is that?

00:20:16.514 --> 00:20:17.657
"Crap?"

00:20:17.657 --> 00:20:19.971
Sometimes animals are better than people.

00:20:19.971 --> 00:20:21.384
Come here, come here.

00:20:21.384 --> 00:20:23.244
Seoltang, are you okay?

00:20:23.244 --> 00:20:25.157
Who is this old guy?

00:20:25.157 --> 00:20:27.049
- What are you doing?
- Are you alright?

00:20:27.049 --> 00:20:29.554
Did you just hit me?

00:20:29.554 --> 00:20:31.343
What?

00:20:31.343 --> 00:20:34.394
I'm already pissed off.

00:20:34.394 --> 00:20:35.591
Say it again. What?

00:20:35.591 --> 00:20:38.144
So what do you want me to do?

00:20:53.902 --> 00:20:56.512
I didn't expect to be summoned
to the police station.

00:20:56.512 --> 00:20:58.071
I thought

00:20:58.071 --> 00:21:01.457
you'd handle this more like an adult.

00:21:06.484 --> 00:21:09.410
Still, our teamwork was pretty good.

00:21:09.410 --> 00:21:13.011
You look quiet, but you've got a temper.

00:21:13.011 --> 00:21:14.435
And you hold grudges.

00:21:14.435 --> 00:21:17.505
It hadn't even been five minutes,
and they were already returning her.

00:21:17.505 --> 00:21:18.582
I just lost it.

00:21:18.582 --> 00:21:20.388
Five minutes is harsh.

00:21:20.388 --> 00:21:22.048
This isn't something to brag about.

00:21:22.048 --> 00:21:25.052
I really wish people would
stop breaking records like this.

00:21:25.052 --> 00:21:26.462
I know.

00:21:26.462 --> 00:21:28.302
Oh no.

00:21:28.302 --> 00:21:29.980
You've got a dog allergy, right?

00:21:29.980 --> 00:21:31.724
I could keep her for now

00:21:31.724 --> 00:21:33.636
and take her back to the shelter this weekend.

00:21:33.636 --> 00:21:35.102
If I take my meds, I'll be fine for a few days.

00:21:35.102 --> 00:21:36.250
I'll keep her.

00:21:36.250 --> 00:21:37.710
Alright then.

00:21:37.710 --> 00:21:39.702
Seoltang,

00:21:39.702 --> 00:21:43.282
maybe you're headed somewhere better, huh?

00:21:47.448 --> 00:21:48.934
That's my phone.

00:21:54.003 --> 00:21:56.547
Sir, I heard my friend made a reservation.

00:21:56.547 --> 00:21:58.020
You even came in on your day off.

00:21:58.020 --> 00:22:00.198
That's another brownie point for you. Thanks.

00:22:00.198 --> 00:22:02.784
You're welcome.

00:22:03.736 --> 00:22:05.335
You're waiting on a call?

00:22:05.335 --> 00:22:08.121
Yes. From Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:22:14.152 --> 00:22:17.102
Well, as the matchmaker,
I do have some responsibility.

00:22:17.102 --> 00:22:19.709
I should probably tell you this
in good conscience.

00:22:19.709 --> 00:22:21.212
About Ms. Ui Yeong...

00:22:21.212 --> 00:22:22.969
I know she's going on other blind dates.

00:22:22.969 --> 00:22:24.978
I saw her with another guy.

00:22:25.612 --> 00:22:27.297
You even saw?

00:22:27.297 --> 00:22:29.632
And you're still waiting?

00:22:29.632 --> 00:22:32.436
Well... she said she'd call.

00:22:32.436 --> 00:22:34.460
And it's not over between us.

00:22:34.460 --> 00:22:36.825
Is that confidence?

00:22:36.825 --> 00:22:39.200
Or are you just clueless?

00:22:39.787 --> 00:22:41.724
If I see her one more time,

00:22:41.724 --> 00:22:44.637
I think I'll know for sure.

00:22:46.961 --> 00:22:48.806
Oh, man.

00:22:48.806 --> 00:22:50.360
Well...

00:22:50.360 --> 00:22:52.377
A matchmaker's just a matchmaker.

00:22:52.377 --> 00:22:54.797
Not Cupid.

00:22:57.415 --> 00:22:59.336
Then...

00:22:59.336 --> 00:23:02.032
Run into her one more time.

00:23:02.032 --> 00:23:03.633
Sorry?

00:23:03.633 --> 00:23:04.650
What do you mean?

00:23:04.650 --> 00:23:07.647
Think of it as warranty service.

00:23:07.647 --> 00:23:09.807
That's how hotels work, right?

00:23:09.807 --> 00:23:11.504
For some, it's a workplace.

00:23:11.504 --> 00:23:14.843
A place they have to stay eight hours a day.

00:23:14.843 --> 00:23:17.694
For others, it's somewhere
you drop by for a meeting

00:23:17.694 --> 00:23:21.107
or a cup of coffee with a friend.

00:23:21.107 --> 00:23:24.920
So... just happen to run into her
one more time.

00:23:30.287 --> 00:23:32.098
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:23:32.098 --> 00:23:34.460
This is the hotel you work at...

00:23:37.990 --> 00:23:41.557
I'm just here to meet a friend.

00:23:44.164 --> 00:23:46.807
Since we ran into each other like this,

00:23:46.807 --> 00:23:50.287
want to grab a bite together?

00:23:50.287 --> 00:23:53.347
Why am I holding her hand?

00:23:54.347 --> 00:23:56.740
Ms. Ui Yeong?

00:23:56.740 --> 00:23:58.084
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:23:58.084 --> 00:24:00.067
Ms. Ui Yeong?

00:24:00.067 --> 00:24:03.040
Ms. Seoltang...

00:24:03.040 --> 00:24:05.545
What do I do?

00:24:05.545 --> 00:24:06.214
[Purchasing Team Conference Room]

00:24:06.214 --> 00:24:07.296
HOME is a brand

00:24:07.296 --> 00:24:09.478
that's been getting a lot of buzz lately

00:24:09.478 --> 00:24:11.689
among people into home styling.

00:24:11.689 --> 00:24:13.559
[Vendor Portfolios]

00:24:13.559 --> 00:24:16.803
They've also done cafe remodels like this.

00:24:16.803 --> 00:24:18.827
We're not playing house.

00:24:18.827 --> 00:24:20.309
We've worked with Homage plenty.

00:24:20.309 --> 00:24:22.028
Let's just go with them.

00:24:22.028 --> 00:24:24.978
Of course Homage is great,
but this looks impressive too.

00:24:24.978 --> 00:24:27.035
Why don't we get proposals from both

00:24:27.035 --> 00:24:29.008
and decide after reviewing them?

00:24:29.008 --> 00:24:30.812
That's more work for us.

00:24:30.812 --> 00:24:32.509
Do we really need to go that far?

00:24:32.509 --> 00:24:35.349
Making sure the space turns out right
is part of our job too.

00:24:35.349 --> 00:24:36.732
Let's request a proposal.

00:24:36.732 --> 00:24:38.459
Should we give them about two weeks?

00:24:38.459 --> 00:24:40.690
Even a rough draft is fine. Make it one week.

00:24:40.690 --> 00:24:42.572
One week might be...

00:24:42.572 --> 00:24:44.237
a bit tight.

00:24:44.237 --> 00:24:46.588
Then let's make it ten days.

00:24:46.588 --> 00:24:48.761
If you're going to decide
everything yourselves,

00:24:48.761 --> 00:24:50.507
why even ask me?

00:24:50.507 --> 00:24:51.957
I'll contact Homage.

00:24:51.957 --> 00:24:53.895
You handle the rest.

00:24:53.895 --> 00:24:55.761
Okay. I'll reach out to HOME.

00:24:55.761 --> 00:24:57.423
Oh, right. Sae Byeok.

00:24:57.423 --> 00:24:59.080
Since she found the vendor,

00:24:59.080 --> 00:25:00.774
why don't we let her handle the contact?

00:25:00.774 --> 00:25:02.352
I'll send the email,

00:25:02.352 --> 00:25:05.287
and she can take care of
the detailed communication.

00:25:05.936 --> 00:25:07.809
Want to give it a try?

00:25:07.809 --> 00:25:11.407
Yes. I'll do it.

00:25:11.407 --> 00:25:14.397
[The Hills & Deerfiddich Whisky Brand Pop-up]
[Designated Bid Proposal]

00:25:14.397 --> 00:25:16.141
[Your email has been sent successfully.]
Done.

00:25:16.141 --> 00:25:17.207
- Sae Byeok.
- Yeah.

00:25:17.207 --> 00:25:18.242
Now that the email's sent,

00:25:18.242 --> 00:25:20.371
give them a call and let's head out.

00:25:20.371 --> 00:25:21.401
Okay.

00:25:21.401 --> 00:25:23.279
- Great work today.
- Good work.

00:25:23.279 --> 00:25:26.041
- You head home early too.
- Yes.

00:25:38.911 --> 00:25:41.015
Hello, this is Lee Eun Ho from HOME.

00:25:41.015 --> 00:25:42.221
Hello,

00:25:42.221 --> 00:25:45.091
this is Sim Sae Byeok
from the Purchasing Team at The Hills.

00:25:45.091 --> 00:25:48.651
I just sent you an email.

00:25:49.738 --> 00:25:51.700
I see.

00:25:51.700 --> 00:25:54.316
- About the pop-up?
- Yes, that's right.

00:25:54.316 --> 00:25:57.064
[Ms. Hyun Min, HOME checked the email
and will get back to us.]

00:26:04.948 --> 00:26:06.914
- Isn't she that intern?
- Who?

00:26:06.914 --> 00:26:08.738
You know, Do Hyun's...

00:26:08.738 --> 00:26:11.458
- Oh, that intern.
- Yeah.

00:26:12.464 --> 00:26:14.862
Interns these days really know
how to make work interesting.

00:26:14.862 --> 00:26:17.348
Tell me about it.

00:26:27.475 --> 00:26:29.039
Attorney Kang,

00:26:29.039 --> 00:26:32.372
may I speak with you for a moment?

00:26:36.900 --> 00:26:39.573
No, stay seated.

00:26:42.206 --> 00:26:43.903
Enjoy your drink.

00:26:43.903 --> 00:26:46.312
Thank you.

00:26:56.638 --> 00:26:59.679
So... have you given it some thought?

00:26:59.679 --> 00:27:01.692
Yes.

00:27:02.599 --> 00:27:06.696
I feel uneasy about Ms. Ui Yeong,

00:27:06.696 --> 00:27:10.869
and right now,
getting a job is my top priority.

00:27:10.869 --> 00:27:13.296
I'm sorry.

00:27:16.149 --> 00:27:19.286
I've been rejected like this before.

00:27:19.286 --> 00:27:22.813
Back then, I had nothing to offer,
so I just backed off.

00:27:22.813 --> 00:27:24.436
But things are different now.

00:27:24.436 --> 00:27:26.263
I can buy you meals,

00:27:26.263 --> 00:27:28.741
I can support you with
what you need for employment.

00:27:28.741 --> 00:27:30.793
You should think about
what would benefit you more...

00:27:30.793 --> 00:27:32.340
To be honest,

00:27:32.340 --> 00:27:33.933
it's actually put me at a disadvantage.

00:27:33.933 --> 00:27:36.030
I haven't even had the chance to prove myself,

00:27:36.030 --> 00:27:38.090
but people at the company already recognize me

00:27:38.090 --> 00:27:40.602
because you said you liked me.

00:27:40.602 --> 00:27:42.326
The project I'm handling this time...

00:27:42.326 --> 00:27:44.790
I'm going to give it everything I've got.

00:27:44.790 --> 00:27:48.196
Please help me focus on my work.

00:27:49.323 --> 00:27:52.836
I'll get going now.

00:28:16.690 --> 00:28:18.621
Do you need more support frames for the legs?

00:28:18.621 --> 00:28:19.652
[The Hills & Deerfiddich Whisky Brand Pop-up]

00:28:19.652 --> 00:28:21.392
We'll simplify the frame
and use straps instead.

00:28:21.392 --> 00:28:23.334
[We would like to propose your company
as a designated bidder.]

00:28:23.334 --> 00:28:25.971
Hey, Lee Eun Ho. Did you see the email?

00:28:25.971 --> 00:28:27.375
- Which one?
- The Hills pop-up.

00:28:27.375 --> 00:28:28.633
Yeah, I saw it.

00:28:28.633 --> 00:28:29.926
But I was going to turn it down.

00:28:29.926 --> 00:28:31.360
Our schedule's already tight,

00:28:31.360 --> 00:28:32.613
and you hate pop-ups anyway.

00:28:32.613 --> 00:28:33.937
All that work for something temporary.

00:28:33.937 --> 00:28:36.904
Yeah, I do hate them.

00:28:36.904 --> 00:28:39.515
But we're doing this one.

00:28:39.515 --> 00:28:40.539
Doing what?

00:28:40.539 --> 00:28:42.254
You don't have to.
We've got plenty to do already.

00:28:42.254 --> 00:28:43.633
No.

00:28:43.633 --> 00:28:45.859
- I want to do it.
- What?

00:28:45.859 --> 00:28:47.103
Where are you going?

00:28:47.103 --> 00:28:48.790
The hotel. To check out the space.

00:28:48.790 --> 00:28:50.300
Right now?

00:28:50.300 --> 00:28:52.194
You're really doing this?

00:28:52.194 --> 00:28:53.304
Yeah.

00:28:53.304 --> 00:28:57.064
I was planning to go today anyway.

00:28:57.064 --> 00:28:58.501
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:28:58.501 --> 00:28:59.687
Yes?

00:28:59.687 --> 00:29:02.904
I heard back from Lee Eun Ho at HOME.

00:29:02.904 --> 00:29:04.524
He said they want to participate in the bid.

00:29:04.524 --> 00:29:06.614
Really? That's great.

00:29:06.614 --> 00:29:10.278
I felt bad dumping all the work
on you and Hyun Min.

00:29:10.278 --> 00:29:13.258
I'll treat you both properly next time.

00:29:27.506 --> 00:29:29.965
So this is the place.

00:29:34.456 --> 00:29:36.956
I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

00:29:36.956 --> 00:29:39.205
I'm okay, thanks.

00:29:49.547 --> 00:29:51.893
I'll see her again... right?

00:29:55.771 --> 00:29:57.635
I need to take this call. Go on ahead.

00:29:57.635 --> 00:29:59.505
Okay.

00:30:01.490 --> 00:30:02.514
Hello?

00:30:02.514 --> 00:30:04.147
Is this Ms. Lee Ui Yeong's phone?

00:30:04.147 --> 00:30:05.697
I got your number from Ms. Eun Mi.

00:30:05.697 --> 00:30:07.117
This is Kim Su On.

00:30:07.117 --> 00:30:09.007
Oh, yeah.

00:30:09.007 --> 00:30:10.414
Hello.

00:30:10.414 --> 00:30:12.564
Sorry for calling out of the blue.

00:30:12.564 --> 00:30:15.824
Are you free tomorrow evening?

00:30:19.592 --> 00:30:21.468
I heard a lot about you from Ms. Eun Mi.

00:30:21.468 --> 00:30:23.271
She kept saying how nice you are.

00:30:23.271 --> 00:30:25.654
I wasn't expecting much looks-wise...

00:30:26.984 --> 00:30:29.408
You're very beautiful.

00:30:29.408 --> 00:30:32.232
[Kim Su On, 35, Family Business Owner]

00:30:32.232 --> 00:30:35.272
Thank you.

00:30:35.272 --> 00:30:36.622
I heard

00:30:36.622 --> 00:30:39.122
you and Mr. Ho Jin
have been friends for a long time.

00:30:39.122 --> 00:30:41.089
Yeah, that punk...

00:30:41.089 --> 00:30:43.679
It's been about twenty years already
with that guy.

00:30:43.679 --> 00:30:44.851
We should go on

00:30:44.851 --> 00:30:46.523
a double date sometime, the four of us.

00:30:46.523 --> 00:30:48.446
Right?

00:30:53.568 --> 00:30:56.621
So what are your parents' hobbies?

00:30:56.621 --> 00:30:59.052
My parents' hobbies?

00:30:59.052 --> 00:31:00.954
Yes.

00:31:01.934 --> 00:31:05.898
My mom has been doing yoga for a long time,

00:31:05.898 --> 00:31:10.388
and my dad used to enjoy fishing and camping,

00:31:10.388 --> 00:31:11.834
but these days he doesn't really...

00:31:11.834 --> 00:31:15.214
I heard your father works for the railway.

00:31:16.151 --> 00:31:17.935
Yes, that's right.

00:31:17.935 --> 00:31:21.258
And that you live separately
because of his job.

00:31:22.509 --> 00:31:25.463
Well, not just because of his job.

00:31:25.463 --> 00:31:28.933
It's my parents' situation,
so I don't know everything,

00:31:28.933 --> 00:31:32.896
but they've lived apart since I was young

00:31:32.896 --> 00:31:35.403
because their personalities
and values are very different.

00:31:37.623 --> 00:31:39.380
So are they divorced?

00:31:39.380 --> 00:31:41.027
No, not divorced.

00:31:41.027 --> 00:31:43.687
- Separated.
- I see.

00:31:43.687 --> 00:31:46.334
Well, that's a relief.

00:31:46.334 --> 00:31:47.359
"A relief?"

00:31:47.359 --> 00:31:49.937
You seem like someone who grew up very loved.

00:31:49.937 --> 00:31:53.217
Honestly, I never would've guessed
if you hadn't told me.

00:32:10.395 --> 00:32:12.748
So tired.

00:32:22.437 --> 00:32:24.015
Oh, Eun Mi.

00:32:24.015 --> 00:32:25.656
Hey, I heard you met Su On today.

00:32:25.656 --> 00:32:28.535
How was he? Isn't he kind of interesting?

00:32:29.461 --> 00:32:32.065
He sure knows how to say
boring things with confidence.

00:32:32.065 --> 00:32:34.172
He's just honest.

00:32:34.172 --> 00:32:35.536
You know what he told me?

00:32:35.536 --> 00:32:38.469
He usually likes girls from happy families,

00:32:38.469 --> 00:32:40.922
but he wants to see you again.

00:32:43.603 --> 00:32:45.193
What does that even mean?

00:32:45.193 --> 00:32:48.106
I heard your parents are living separately.

00:32:48.106 --> 00:32:50.703
Why didn't you tell me?

00:32:50.703 --> 00:32:52.663
I never hid it.

00:32:52.663 --> 00:32:54.887
You don't have to share everything
to be friends.

00:32:54.887 --> 00:32:56.007
The point is,

00:32:56.007 --> 00:32:57.117
he wants a second date.

00:32:57.117 --> 00:32:58.964
That means it went well.

00:32:58.964 --> 00:33:00.382
Oh, and he's wondering

00:33:00.382 --> 00:33:03.137
if your parents are financially prepared
for retirement.

00:33:03.137 --> 00:33:04.971
What?

00:33:04.971 --> 00:33:06.541
Why would he want to know that?

00:33:06.541 --> 00:33:08.565
Well, it's good for you to know too.

00:33:08.565 --> 00:33:10.011
It doesn't have to be detailed.

00:33:10.011 --> 00:33:12.684
Just a simple yes or no.

00:33:13.430 --> 00:33:15.606
He's asking way too much.

00:33:15.606 --> 00:33:17.802
I'm hanging up.

00:34:28.375 --> 00:34:30.545
[Dad]

00:34:34.042 --> 00:34:35.799
I can't just call my dad

00:34:35.799 --> 00:34:38.412
and ask about retirement.

00:34:43.655 --> 00:34:46.028
Mom?

00:34:46.028 --> 00:34:47.099
What are you doing?

00:34:47.099 --> 00:34:49.078
Nothing.

00:34:50.622 --> 00:34:52.492
Don't stay up too late on your phone.

00:34:52.492 --> 00:34:54.552
I'm not a high schooler anymore.

00:34:54.552 --> 00:34:56.378
Good night.

00:35:04.089 --> 00:35:06.422
Yeah, this really isn't right.

00:35:06.422 --> 00:35:07.752
My parents' retirement?

00:35:07.752 --> 00:35:11.035
I dated just fine
without knowing stuff like that.

00:35:14.914 --> 00:35:18.586
I don't think Mr. Su On and I are a good match.

00:35:18.586 --> 00:35:21.386
Tell him for me, okay?

00:35:26.552 --> 00:35:28.512
Alright.

00:35:29.895 --> 00:35:31.894
What's this?

00:35:32.755 --> 00:35:34.912
I still have something with the tag on.

00:35:34.912 --> 00:35:37.598
Nice. I can return it.

00:35:39.850 --> 00:35:42.183
Oh my, that's a lot.

00:35:42.183 --> 00:35:43.841
- By this week.
- What?

00:35:43.841 --> 00:35:46.122
Get it done by the end of the week.

00:36:13.289 --> 00:36:15.739
We said we'd get proposals
from the vendors, right?

00:36:15.739 --> 00:36:17.709
Let's just review Homage and be done with it.

00:36:17.709 --> 00:36:19.323
Sorry? Why?

00:36:19.323 --> 00:36:22.027
It's a waste of time.
When would we review all that?

00:36:22.027 --> 00:36:24.238
Honestly, we were going with Homage anyway.

00:36:24.238 --> 00:36:27.281
They just did that to give you the job.

00:36:27.281 --> 00:36:29.245
Let's not make things complicated.

00:36:29.245 --> 00:36:32.955
Then I'll just check with Ms. Ui Yeong first...

00:36:32.955 --> 00:36:34.979
You're saying you need Ui Yeong's approval

00:36:34.979 --> 00:36:38.145
for what I just said?

00:36:38.145 --> 00:36:40.965
No, that's not what I meant.

00:36:40.965 --> 00:36:43.265
Sorry.

00:36:44.657 --> 00:36:46.067
- Ms. Sae Byeok.
- Yes.

00:36:46.067 --> 00:36:49.077
Handling situations like this
is part of the job.

00:36:49.077 --> 00:36:53.294
I'll make sure this proposal
turns out perfect on my side.

00:36:53.294 --> 00:36:56.095
Just wrap things up cleanly
so the other vendor doesn't make a fuss.

00:36:56.095 --> 00:36:58.557
Yes, understood.

00:37:08.491 --> 00:37:11.604
[Conference Room]
Hello.

00:37:11.604 --> 00:37:13.221
I'm Oh Man Joong, CEO of Homage.

00:37:13.221 --> 00:37:16.874
Even your business card looks impressive.

00:37:20.310 --> 00:37:22.374
We successfully wrapped up the exhibition

00:37:22.374 --> 00:37:23.914
at Place Hotel earlier this year,

00:37:23.914 --> 00:37:26.593
and what was the other one... last week?

00:37:26.593 --> 00:37:27.741
Oh right,

00:37:27.741 --> 00:37:29.518
the Bella Museum.

00:37:29.518 --> 00:37:31.011
As we mentioned in the email,

00:37:31.011 --> 00:37:33.774
our exhibition will focus on objects.

00:37:33.774 --> 00:37:35.671
So we just need to build some showcases.

00:37:35.671 --> 00:37:37.942
Let me show you the jewelry store opening

00:37:37.942 --> 00:37:40.108
we did at New World Department Store in 2017.

00:37:40.108 --> 00:37:42.028
Yes.

00:37:49.084 --> 00:37:51.617
Here it is.

00:37:53.694 --> 00:37:55.504
Next is the delivery schedule.

00:37:55.504 --> 00:37:57.028
Construction needs to be completed at least...

00:37:57.028 --> 00:37:58.221
Miss?

00:37:58.221 --> 00:37:59.581
We're not some small-time shop.

00:37:59.581 --> 00:38:01.811
We've done pop-ups like this in our sleep.

00:38:01.811 --> 00:38:03.840
You think a company that collaborates with

00:38:03.840 --> 00:38:05.308
city halls and department stores

00:38:05.308 --> 00:38:07.172
can't meet a deadline?

00:38:07.172 --> 00:38:08.463
Of course, but

00:38:08.463 --> 00:38:09.804
we just need to confirm the process...

00:38:09.804 --> 00:38:11.954
Ms. Sara, show them the proposal.

00:38:11.954 --> 00:38:13.860
Yes.

00:38:16.594 --> 00:38:19.373
Oh wow, already?

00:38:22.100 --> 00:38:24.073
Wow.

00:38:27.398 --> 00:38:28.990
You prepared something this detailed

00:38:28.990 --> 00:38:31.148
in such a short time?

00:38:31.148 --> 00:38:33.618
We'll use lauan plywood

00:38:33.618 --> 00:38:36.162
to bring out the vintage mood of a whisky bar.

00:38:36.162 --> 00:38:38.879
Some of the wood surfaces
will be finished with Formica

00:38:38.879 --> 00:38:42.365
to highlight Deerfiddich's signature color.

00:38:42.365 --> 00:38:44.975
Such high quality in so little time.

00:38:44.975 --> 00:38:47.763
Professionals really are different.

00:38:47.763 --> 00:38:50.589
What do you think, Manager?

00:38:50.589 --> 00:38:52.902
Looks good.

00:38:58.411 --> 00:39:01.211
It looks so classy.

00:39:01.211 --> 00:39:02.886
- Thank you for your time.
- Thank you.

00:39:02.886 --> 00:39:05.059
- Thank you for coming.
- This way, please.

00:39:05.059 --> 00:39:07.696
Thank you so much, Mr. Oh.

00:39:07.696 --> 00:39:09.906
And you look very stylish today too.

00:39:09.906 --> 00:39:10.991
You're too kind.

00:39:10.991 --> 00:39:12.601
If your schedule allows,

00:39:12.601 --> 00:39:16.067
maybe we could grab a drink.

00:39:19.170 --> 00:39:20.646
Hey, Sae Byeok.

00:39:20.646 --> 00:39:25.773
Have you scheduled the meeting
with the CEO of HOME yet?

00:39:25.773 --> 00:39:28.197
Actually... you know...

00:39:28.197 --> 00:39:31.390
I heard back from him...

00:39:32.224 --> 00:39:34.473
but...

00:39:34.473 --> 00:39:36.777
due to internal reasons,

00:39:36.777 --> 00:39:39.776
there's been a change of plans,

00:39:40.464 --> 00:39:41.947
and they said they have to drop out.

00:39:41.947 --> 00:39:43.261
Drop out?

00:39:43.261 --> 00:39:47.307
After the project's already underway?

00:39:51.255 --> 00:39:53.959
So that's why you looked down earlier.

00:39:53.959 --> 00:39:56.616
You worked hard on this.
That must be disappointing.

00:39:56.616 --> 00:39:59.413
It's okay. This happens sometimes.

00:39:59.413 --> 00:40:00.720
Yeah.

00:40:00.720 --> 00:40:01.837
Still,

00:40:01.837 --> 00:40:04.401
I'm just glad we get to work with

00:40:04.401 --> 00:40:07.290
such capable people.

00:40:07.290 --> 00:40:08.807
Yeah, don't worry.

00:40:08.807 --> 00:40:10.707
Okay.

00:40:14.883 --> 00:40:17.683
- Let's wrap up.
- Okay.

00:40:27.778 --> 00:40:30.905
Is this exhibition flow too complicated?

00:40:30.905 --> 00:40:32.575
Oh, I like it.

00:40:32.575 --> 00:40:34.171
Yeah.

00:40:34.171 --> 00:40:36.691
Looks great, but...

00:40:37.392 --> 00:40:39.812
we're out.

00:40:39.812 --> 00:40:41.845
What?

00:40:41.845 --> 00:40:45.018
We haven't even had the meeting yet.

00:40:45.925 --> 00:40:47.655
Got a cigarette?

00:40:47.655 --> 00:40:49.808
I quit a long time ago.

00:40:50.738 --> 00:40:53.833
It pisses me off that
they just canceled over "internal reasons."

00:40:53.833 --> 00:40:56.985
Usually they at least say
the budget didn't work out.

00:40:56.985 --> 00:40:59.009
This is just plain disrespectful.

00:40:59.009 --> 00:41:01.742
They probably already had a vendor lined up.

00:41:01.742 --> 00:41:04.712
That excuse is way too obvious.

00:41:04.712 --> 00:41:06.216
If that's really the case,

00:41:06.216 --> 00:41:10.198
maybe it's better things ended now.

00:41:10.198 --> 00:41:13.552
You stayed up for days
trying to match their plans, didn't you?

00:41:13.552 --> 00:41:16.345
Want to get some air?

00:41:16.345 --> 00:41:19.998
Yeah. Let's take Sua out for a bit.

00:41:26.489 --> 00:41:29.055
- Good work today.
- Thank you.

00:41:30.047 --> 00:41:31.424
Hello?

00:41:31.424 --> 00:41:33.744
Guess you didn't save my number.

00:41:33.744 --> 00:41:35.848
This is Su On.

00:41:35.848 --> 00:41:39.005
I asked Ms. Eun Mi to tell you
I wanted to see you again.

00:41:39.005 --> 00:41:41.816
Did Eun Mi not pass along what I said?

00:41:41.816 --> 00:41:43.467
Are you free after work?

00:41:43.467 --> 00:41:44.769
I've got something to take care of.

00:41:44.769 --> 00:41:46.912
I happen to be near your hotel.

00:41:46.912 --> 00:41:49.613
Oh, really?

00:41:49.613 --> 00:41:52.533
Yes, I'm available.

00:41:53.646 --> 00:41:55.506
Okay.

00:42:05.059 --> 00:42:08.839
I actually brought this to return...

00:42:17.256 --> 00:42:18.507
Ms. Ui Yeong.

00:42:18.507 --> 00:42:21.863
That outfit looks really good on you today.

00:42:21.863 --> 00:42:25.370
Pink's not easy to pull off.

00:42:25.370 --> 00:42:27.683
Thank you.

00:42:27.683 --> 00:42:29.800
Mr. Su On,

00:42:29.800 --> 00:42:33.893
I heard you were asking
about my parents' retirement plans.

00:42:33.893 --> 00:42:34.917
Yes.

00:42:34.917 --> 00:42:37.253
Why?

00:42:37.253 --> 00:42:38.850
Well... this is just my opinion, but

00:42:38.850 --> 00:42:42.137
we're not meeting with marriage
in mind right now,

00:42:42.137 --> 00:42:43.667
and my parents' retirement

00:42:43.667 --> 00:42:46.554
is something for me
and my parents to figure out.

00:42:46.554 --> 00:42:50.974
It's not something you need to plan for.

00:42:50.974 --> 00:42:52.961
Oh, I see.

00:42:52.961 --> 00:42:54.748
That's fair.

00:42:54.748 --> 00:42:57.561
Don't worry about it.

00:42:59.848 --> 00:43:01.593
Let's change the mood a bit.

00:43:01.593 --> 00:43:03.372
How about a bottle of wine?

00:43:03.372 --> 00:43:05.552
Okay.

00:43:05.552 --> 00:43:08.352
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

00:43:11.025 --> 00:43:14.585
Can we have a cheese platter
and a bottle of wine?

00:43:15.800 --> 00:43:17.733
This one, please.

00:43:17.733 --> 00:43:21.226
- Lee Jeong Woo?
- I'll bring that right out.

00:43:37.092 --> 00:43:38.964
[Shin Ji Su]

00:43:38.964 --> 00:43:40.314
Oh right...

00:43:40.314 --> 00:43:44.067
If it's Lee Jeong Woo,
he should have a tattoo on his neck.

00:43:59.961 --> 00:44:01.985
I heard you can drink pretty well.

00:44:01.985 --> 00:44:04.812
What's your actual limit?

00:44:04.812 --> 00:44:06.663
Well, it depends on what I'm drinking.

00:44:06.663 --> 00:44:07.996
For wine... maybe a bottle?

00:44:07.996 --> 00:44:09.973
That's way more than me.

00:44:09.973 --> 00:44:13.008
I guess I'll have to pour you a bit more
to keep up with you.

00:44:13.008 --> 00:44:14.704
Yeah.

00:44:14.704 --> 00:44:16.016
Excuse me,

00:44:16.016 --> 00:44:18.105
I need to use the restroom.

00:44:18.105 --> 00:44:20.244
Sure.

00:44:26.930 --> 00:44:29.183
Excuse me.

00:44:30.397 --> 00:44:34.290
This might be an odd question, but...

00:44:34.290 --> 00:44:37.577
are you by any chance a twin?

00:44:37.577 --> 00:44:39.824
No, I'm an only child.

00:44:39.824 --> 00:44:43.277
Oh... sorry about that.

00:44:44.151 --> 00:44:46.174
If it were twins,

00:44:46.174 --> 00:44:48.848
wouldn't the last names match?

00:44:48.848 --> 00:44:50.121
Huh?

00:44:50.121 --> 00:44:51.765
I'm Shin,

00:44:51.765 --> 00:44:54.278
and the person you know is Lee.

00:44:54.278 --> 00:44:56.977
Right, that's true.

00:44:58.664 --> 00:45:00.625
It is you, isn't it?

00:45:00.625 --> 00:45:02.090
Lee Jeong Woo.

00:45:02.090 --> 00:45:03.387
What are you doing here?

00:45:03.387 --> 00:45:04.626
Isn't it obvious?

00:45:04.626 --> 00:45:08.121
- I'm working part-time.
- I mean why are you here?

00:45:08.121 --> 00:45:10.428
Another blind date?

00:45:10.428 --> 00:45:12.727
You really want a relationship, huh?

00:45:12.727 --> 00:45:13.477
What?

00:45:13.477 --> 00:45:17.567
You kept going on about dating last time too.

00:45:19.108 --> 00:45:20.958
The guy's not bad.

00:45:20.958 --> 00:45:24.030
He's got eyes, a nose, a mouth.

00:45:24.030 --> 00:45:26.031
He dresses well too.

00:45:26.031 --> 00:45:28.011
Just your type.

00:45:28.011 --> 00:45:29.395
And what exactly is my type?

00:45:29.395 --> 00:45:30.781
Good luck.

00:45:30.781 --> 00:45:34.368
But if you end up not liking him,

00:45:34.368 --> 00:45:36.614
just do this.

00:45:36.614 --> 00:45:39.001
Like this. Send me a signal.

00:45:39.001 --> 00:45:40.574
Okay?

00:45:40.574 --> 00:45:42.507
Hey...

00:45:46.380 --> 00:45:49.452
What is wrong with him?

00:46:04.807 --> 00:46:06.133
Well...

00:46:06.133 --> 00:46:07.418
Mr. Su On,

00:46:07.418 --> 00:46:11.791
I think we should move somewhere
more comfortable.

00:46:13.173 --> 00:46:14.423
Oh, okay.

00:46:14.423 --> 00:46:15.949
Do you have somewhere in mind?

00:46:15.949 --> 00:46:18.170
No place in particular.

00:46:18.170 --> 00:46:19.568
Anywhere's fine.

00:46:19.568 --> 00:46:20.972
Just not here.

00:46:20.972 --> 00:46:24.340
Anywhere is fine?

00:46:24.340 --> 00:46:25.570
Sounds good.

00:46:25.570 --> 00:46:27.415
Let me use the restroom first.

00:46:27.415 --> 00:46:29.515
Sure.

00:46:41.335 --> 00:46:43.359
What is wrong with him...

00:46:43.359 --> 00:46:45.272
Ms. Eun Mi told me

00:46:45.272 --> 00:46:48.178
she turned down the second date.

00:46:49.232 --> 00:46:52.562
She's nothing special, and she turns me down?

00:46:52.562 --> 00:46:54.972
I just called her out because I was bored.

00:46:54.972 --> 00:46:57.605
You know what really killed the mood?

00:46:57.605 --> 00:47:00.670
She came out with the tag still on her clothes.

00:47:00.670 --> 00:47:03.040
If I take the tag off for her,

00:47:03.040 --> 00:47:05.613
does that make her mine?

00:47:06.312 --> 00:47:08.579
Beats me.

00:47:09.665 --> 00:47:11.892
Yeah.

00:47:11.892 --> 00:47:14.898
She wants to move somewhere more comfortable.

00:47:14.898 --> 00:47:18.277
Where should we go? A nice motel?

00:47:19.325 --> 00:47:21.461
It's slippery.

00:47:21.461 --> 00:47:24.427
Sorry about that.

00:47:27.236 --> 00:47:29.210
What?

00:47:30.403 --> 00:47:34.276
There's no water here...

00:47:37.524 --> 00:47:38.834
Let's go.

00:47:38.834 --> 00:47:40.681
- What are you doing?
- I'll explain outside.

00:47:40.681 --> 00:47:43.145
- Hey, let go.
- What's going on?

00:47:43.145 --> 00:47:44.965
Mr. Su On, it's just...

00:47:44.965 --> 00:47:46.495
Ui Yeong,

00:47:46.495 --> 00:47:49.109
looks like your taste in men has changed.

00:47:49.109 --> 00:47:50.402
You...

00:47:50.402 --> 00:47:52.425
You shoved me on purpose
in the restroom, didn't you?

00:47:52.425 --> 00:47:53.929
Do you know him?

00:47:53.929 --> 00:47:55.963
No, I don't know him. Let's just go.

00:47:55.963 --> 00:47:58.168
You're really leaving?

00:47:58.168 --> 00:48:00.694
- I know how you feel.
- What?

00:48:00.694 --> 00:48:03.446
You came because
you wanted to see me, didn't you?

00:48:03.446 --> 00:48:04.862
What's wrong with you?

00:48:04.862 --> 00:48:07.363
I couldn't sleep or eat because I missed you.

00:48:07.363 --> 00:48:09.854
Look at me. Don't I look thinner?

00:48:09.854 --> 00:48:10.905
Hey.

00:48:12.589 --> 00:48:14.340
So you were using me.

00:48:14.340 --> 00:48:15.242
What?

00:48:15.242 --> 00:48:17.656
Unbelievable.

00:48:17.656 --> 00:48:19.453
You act all classy,

00:48:19.453 --> 00:48:21.281
but your situation with men is a mess.

00:48:21.281 --> 00:48:23.084
Who's the real mess here?

00:48:23.084 --> 00:48:24.043
You hit me?

00:48:24.043 --> 00:48:25.510
Hey, stop!

00:48:25.510 --> 00:48:27.034
- Stop it!
- Darn it.

00:48:27.034 --> 00:48:29.381
Stop...

00:48:29.381 --> 00:48:31.531
- Are you...
- What's going on?

00:48:31.531 --> 00:48:33.690
Are you okay?

00:48:33.690 --> 00:48:36.876
You pushed me first.

00:48:38.163 --> 00:48:40.350
Oh gosh.

00:48:41.330 --> 00:48:44.070
I'm sorry.

00:48:56.592 --> 00:48:58.998
I'll take you home.

00:48:58.998 --> 00:49:01.865
Why would you take me home?

00:49:01.865 --> 00:49:04.085
You had wine.

00:49:04.085 --> 00:49:06.369
First you interfere,
then you act like you care.

00:49:06.369 --> 00:49:08.120
Make up your mind.

00:49:08.120 --> 00:49:10.213
Is there some reason for this?

00:49:10.213 --> 00:49:13.469
Tell me so I can understand.

00:49:13.469 --> 00:49:15.702
Well...

00:49:16.976 --> 00:49:18.893
You tucked your hair behind your ear.

00:49:18.893 --> 00:49:20.351
I thought it was a signal.

00:49:20.351 --> 00:49:22.979
That you wanted me to rescue you.

00:49:26.916 --> 00:49:28.990
Do I look that pathetic to you?

00:49:28.990 --> 00:49:30.484
"Why does she live like this?"

00:49:30.484 --> 00:49:32.403
"Why is she so desperate for love?"
That's what you think, isn't it?

00:49:32.403 --> 00:49:33.931
That's not it.

00:49:33.931 --> 00:49:35.108
But you know what?

00:49:35.108 --> 00:49:36.828
You're even more ridiculous.

00:49:36.828 --> 00:49:40.134
So funny I can't even laugh.

00:49:41.477 --> 00:49:43.528
You're fake.

00:49:43.528 --> 00:49:46.862
The blind date was fake, your name was fake.

00:49:46.862 --> 00:49:48.978
And someone like you thinks I'm ridiculous...

00:49:48.978 --> 00:49:51.878
Why wouldn't I find you ridiculous?

00:50:37.906 --> 00:50:39.991
How long are you going to keep following me?

00:50:39.991 --> 00:50:42.703
Until you calm down.

00:50:42.703 --> 00:50:45.362
What's with him?

00:50:45.362 --> 00:50:48.002
Just go now.

00:50:53.650 --> 00:50:54.841
[The Seagull]

00:50:54.841 --> 00:50:56.396
Here.

00:50:56.396 --> 00:50:58.270
What is this?

00:50:58.270 --> 00:51:01.602
My name's not Lee Jeong Woo. It's Shin Ji Su.

00:51:01.602 --> 00:51:03.447
I'm an actor.

00:51:03.447 --> 00:51:06.230
I'm twenty-nine.

00:51:06.230 --> 00:51:08.827
I went on that blind date for someone else
because of a situation.

00:51:08.827 --> 00:51:11.660
And the reason is...

00:51:12.432 --> 00:51:15.218
I can't tell you.

00:51:15.218 --> 00:51:17.294
I'm not curious about your story.

00:51:17.294 --> 00:51:20.460
Even if I knew, it wouldn't change anything.

00:51:22.109 --> 00:51:24.359
Just take it.

00:51:24.359 --> 00:51:26.453
It's basically my ID.

00:51:26.453 --> 00:51:30.399
I just didn't want to be
completely fake with you.

00:51:34.842 --> 00:51:37.079
I don't understand you.

00:51:37.079 --> 00:51:40.612
I don't get why you want love that badly.

00:51:40.612 --> 00:51:41.817
But

00:51:41.817 --> 00:51:45.025
I've never once looked down on you.

00:51:49.687 --> 00:51:52.251
Okay. Just go.

00:51:52.251 --> 00:51:54.589
Wait.

00:52:14.906 --> 00:52:16.244
What?

00:52:16.244 --> 00:52:17.747
What did you just do?

00:52:17.747 --> 00:52:19.260
Well...

00:52:19.260 --> 00:52:22.866
You had something on your back.

00:52:26.838 --> 00:52:29.704
Please come see the play.

00:52:30.551 --> 00:52:33.251
I'll get going then.

00:53:23.040 --> 00:53:24.143
- Yeah.
- Hey.

00:53:24.143 --> 00:53:26.807
Why haven't you been answering?

00:53:26.807 --> 00:53:29.200
Are you outside?

00:53:31.147 --> 00:53:32.998
Are you okay?

00:53:32.998 --> 00:53:34.275
Your voice sounded really off.

00:53:34.275 --> 00:53:36.224
I even canceled my PT session and came.

00:53:36.224 --> 00:53:38.771
I'm not okay.

00:53:38.771 --> 00:53:40.484
Two guys got into a fight because of me.

00:53:40.484 --> 00:53:42.467
It was a total mess.

00:53:42.467 --> 00:53:45.774
I was too scared.

00:53:45.774 --> 00:53:48.624
What did you even do on that blind date?

00:53:48.624 --> 00:53:51.054
You look really pale.

00:53:51.054 --> 00:53:52.368
I told you.

00:53:52.368 --> 00:53:54.065
When you rush into things, it backfires.

00:53:54.065 --> 00:53:55.676
Like after a hard workout...

00:53:55.676 --> 00:53:58.035
- You should rest...
- Seung Jun said

00:53:58.035 --> 00:54:00.482
after you push your body too hard,

00:54:00.482 --> 00:54:02.893
- you have to rest.
- You take a break before the next one.

00:54:02.893 --> 00:54:06.092
That's how you avoid getting hurt.

00:54:06.092 --> 00:54:08.570
- He said it's the same with your heart.
- Are you some kind of blind date pro?

00:54:08.570 --> 00:54:11.559
When I give you advice, at least listen.

00:54:21.732 --> 00:54:23.824
[Lee Hyun Ju]
[Are you still open to blind dates?]

00:54:27.210 --> 00:54:31.017
So I decided to take a break
from blind dates for a while.

00:54:31.017 --> 00:54:32.835
I wasn't giving up.

00:54:32.835 --> 00:54:34.868
It was more like crouching down

00:54:34.868 --> 00:54:37.601
to build momentum for later.

00:54:38.566 --> 00:54:40.374
Guys,

00:54:40.374 --> 00:54:41.914
let's call it a day.

00:54:41.914 --> 00:54:43.138
- Huh?
- Sorry?

00:54:43.138 --> 00:54:45.491
You've been covering my workload too.

00:54:45.491 --> 00:54:49.510
Today's on me. For everything!

00:54:50.181 --> 00:54:52.221
That's awkward.

00:55:00.325 --> 00:55:02.582
- Does it look okay?
- Yes.

00:55:02.582 --> 00:55:04.137
Sae Byeok!

00:55:04.137 --> 00:55:08.071
- Did it really not hurt?
- Not at all.

00:55:08.071 --> 00:55:09.601
Shouldn't you go first, Ui Yeong?

00:55:09.601 --> 00:55:10.949
You were worried about your dark spots.

00:55:10.949 --> 00:55:12.674
You know maintenance is everything, huh?

00:55:12.674 --> 00:55:14.578
This is super popular these days.

00:55:14.578 --> 00:55:16.820
I'm kind of scared though.

00:55:16.820 --> 00:55:17.865
Go on.

00:55:17.865 --> 00:55:20.593
Please take good care of her.

00:55:33.341 --> 00:55:36.181
It really doesn't hurt at all.

00:55:39.787 --> 00:55:41.277
Wait, wait!

00:55:41.277 --> 00:55:43.417
Hold on, hold on.

00:55:43.417 --> 00:55:46.137
That feels amazing.

00:55:47.797 --> 00:55:50.083
So nice.

00:55:51.130 --> 00:55:53.763
- Did you like it?
- Yes.

00:55:53.763 --> 00:55:57.143
Ui Yeong, you are the best.

00:55:59.455 --> 00:56:02.996
[Dad]

00:56:02.996 --> 00:56:05.401
[How have you been...]

00:56:05.401 --> 00:56:07.176
How have you been?

00:56:07.176 --> 00:56:08.674
I was working on something else recently,

00:56:08.674 --> 00:56:10.737
and you came to mind, so I'm reaching out.

00:56:10.737 --> 00:56:14.250
Stay healthy.

00:56:21.061 --> 00:56:23.280
But what needed to be set straight,

00:56:23.280 --> 00:56:25.854
had to be set straight.

00:56:26.467 --> 00:56:30.051
I definitely told him
you turned down the second date.

00:56:30.051 --> 00:56:34.664
So what, he just pretended not to know
and called you anyway?

00:56:34.664 --> 00:56:37.692
If you told him, that's enough.

00:56:37.692 --> 00:56:39.456
He's kind of weird.

00:56:39.456 --> 00:56:40.796
Are you okay?

00:56:40.796 --> 00:56:43.153
- You're not hurt, are you?
- No.

00:56:43.153 --> 00:56:44.523
He didn't shove me.

00:56:44.523 --> 00:56:46.121
He pushed one of the staff members.

00:56:46.121 --> 00:56:49.473
I was startled at the time, but I'm fine now.

00:56:49.473 --> 00:56:52.240
Hold on a second.

00:56:56.294 --> 00:56:59.430
Did you know about this or not?

00:56:59.430 --> 00:57:02.729
You two have been friends
for twenty years, right?

00:57:03.490 --> 00:57:07.641
Don't screw this up,
unless you want your engagement called off.

00:57:07.641 --> 00:57:10.888
Yeah, I just heard all this from Ui Yeong.

00:57:13.708 --> 00:57:16.651
[Tasting Event]
What are you talking about?

00:57:27.812 --> 00:57:29.920
Are you sure?

00:57:32.299 --> 00:57:33.985
Where are the parties involved right now?

00:57:33.985 --> 00:57:35.953
They're in the lobby.

00:57:35.953 --> 00:57:39.626
- Team Manager.
- Ms. Ui Yeong, just a moment.

00:57:40.986 --> 00:57:43.026
Ui Yeong!

00:57:43.026 --> 00:57:46.187
Have you seen this?

00:57:46.187 --> 00:57:47.397
[Pop-Up Exhibition at The Hills Seoul
Accused of Using Copycat Design]

00:57:47.397 --> 00:57:49.947
Copycat design?

00:57:55.530 --> 00:57:58.556
Someone needs to take responsibility
for what happened today.

00:57:58.556 --> 00:58:00.393
We sincerely apologize.

00:58:00.393 --> 00:58:02.160
I will make sure this is resolved.

00:58:02.160 --> 00:58:04.826
I'm very sorry.

00:58:11.213 --> 00:58:13.391
[Pop-Up Exhibition at The Hills Seoul
Accused of Using Copycat Design]

00:58:13.391 --> 00:58:14.908
[Is Its Credibility at Risk?]

00:58:14.908 --> 00:58:17.548
This is bold.

00:58:17.548 --> 00:58:19.418
And this was from last year?

00:58:19.418 --> 00:58:22.404
The tip came from the PR team at the museum
where the event was held.

00:58:22.404 --> 00:58:24.268
We've stated that we were unaware,

00:58:24.268 --> 00:58:27.094
but we can't say we're free of responsibility.

00:58:27.094 --> 00:58:29.772
It looks like there was already
a similar dispute before.

00:58:29.772 --> 00:58:32.370
Didn't the Purchasing Team vet the vendor?

00:58:32.370 --> 00:58:33.908
You didn't go ahead with it
knowing that, did you?

00:58:33.908 --> 00:58:36.371
What do you take us for?

00:58:36.371 --> 00:58:37.935
Of course not.

00:58:37.935 --> 00:58:40.973
Weren't we supposed to get a proposal
from another vendor as well?

00:58:40.973 --> 00:58:42.406
They had a strong portfolio.

00:58:42.406 --> 00:58:44.626
The vendor withdrew midway.

00:58:44.626 --> 00:58:46.463
It seemed like an internal issue,
so we didn't press further.

00:58:46.463 --> 00:58:48.263
We didn't drop them.

00:58:48.263 --> 00:58:51.893
Even if we take a loss,
we need to move forward with the event.

00:58:51.893 --> 00:58:53.090
If this ends like this,

00:58:53.090 --> 00:58:55.784
the hotel's reputation
could collapse overnight.

00:58:55.784 --> 00:58:58.793
If the brand raises an issue,
we'll have to compensate them anyway.

00:58:58.793 --> 00:59:01.556
We're better off taking control now
and resolving this ourselves.

00:59:01.556 --> 00:59:03.446
Then take responsibility and redo it.

00:59:03.446 --> 00:59:06.553
Sales and Marketing Team,
don't worry about the budget.

00:59:06.553 --> 00:59:07.664
- Got it.
- Purchasing Team,

00:59:07.664 --> 00:59:09.777
can you find another vendor
to handle the spatial design?

00:59:09.777 --> 00:59:10.930
We'll make it happen.

00:59:10.930 --> 00:59:12.232
Since the schedule's changed,

00:59:12.232 --> 00:59:16.073
we'll also reach back out to the vendors
that were planning to bid.

00:59:24.738 --> 00:59:26.260
Mrs. Na Ri...

00:59:26.260 --> 00:59:28.462
Hey.

00:59:28.462 --> 00:59:31.085
What is this? This is embarrassing.

00:59:31.085 --> 00:59:33.461
- You said you'd handle it yourself.
- Sorry.

00:59:33.461 --> 00:59:36.259
We'll take full responsibility.

00:59:51.057 --> 00:59:53.104
That startled you, right?

00:59:53.104 --> 00:59:55.267
Stuff like this happens
when you work long enough.

00:59:55.267 --> 00:59:57.182
I'll try to persuade them again.

00:59:57.182 --> 01:00:00.254
Send me the phone number of HOME's CEO.

01:00:00.254 --> 01:00:03.314
He's not going to take your call.

01:00:03.314 --> 01:00:06.072
Actually, they didn't cancel the meeting.

01:00:06.072 --> 01:00:08.181
What?

01:00:08.181 --> 01:00:11.388
I canceled it.

01:00:11.388 --> 01:00:12.751
What do you mean?

01:00:12.751 --> 01:00:14.451
Why would you do that?

01:00:14.451 --> 01:00:16.654
Mrs. Na Ri said...

01:00:16.654 --> 01:00:18.851
said we should just move forward with Homage.

01:00:18.851 --> 01:00:21.016
She said she'd take responsibility.

01:00:21.016 --> 01:00:24.679
So I thought I should wrap things up
on my end first...

01:00:24.679 --> 01:00:25.472
What?

01:00:25.472 --> 01:00:29.062
And Homage copied HOME's work.

01:00:29.756 --> 01:00:30.834
What?

01:00:30.834 --> 01:00:34.614
You gave me a chance and I blew it.
I'm so sorry.

01:00:38.768 --> 01:00:41.641
This is a complete mess.

01:00:49.063 --> 01:00:50.628
Hello?

01:00:50.628 --> 01:00:53.204
Is this CEO Lee Eun Ho?

01:00:53.204 --> 01:00:54.855
Yes, it is.

01:00:54.855 --> 01:00:58.618
Hi, this is Lee Ui Yeong
from The Hills Purchasing Team.

01:00:58.618 --> 01:01:00.762
I've been trying to reach you,

01:01:00.762 --> 01:01:03.358
but I couldn't get through.

01:01:03.358 --> 01:01:05.756
Oh, really?

01:01:05.756 --> 01:01:09.276
Well, if it's The Hills...

01:01:09.276 --> 01:01:11.406
I didn't take the calls on purpose.

01:01:11.406 --> 01:01:13.306
I saw the article.

01:01:13.306 --> 01:01:15.730
I was curious what kind of amazing proposal

01:01:15.730 --> 01:01:17.840
made you cancel our meeting.

01:01:17.840 --> 01:01:20.367
Turns out it was a direct copy of our work.

01:01:20.367 --> 01:01:22.271
You must've been very upset.

01:01:22.271 --> 01:01:25.304
I'd like to speak with you about that.

01:01:25.304 --> 01:01:27.429
Are you at the office right now?

01:01:27.429 --> 01:01:28.660
Even if you come, you won't see me.

01:01:28.660 --> 01:01:30.213
I'm heading out now.

01:01:30.213 --> 01:01:33.071
Then may I ask where you're headed?

01:01:33.071 --> 01:01:35.785
I can come to you.

01:01:35.785 --> 01:01:38.735
You're going to chase me down wherever I go?

01:01:38.735 --> 01:01:42.513
Fine. I'm heading to Chuncheon.
Why don't you try coming there?

01:01:42.513 --> 01:01:45.086
- Alright, let's go.
- Hello?

01:01:45.086 --> 01:01:47.179
Let's go.

01:02:17.097 --> 01:02:21.456
He's definitely still inside.
He answered the phone.

01:02:59.783 --> 01:03:02.734
Did he really just leave?

01:03:02.734 --> 01:03:06.694
I don't even know where he is.
I can't just track him down.

01:03:16.851 --> 01:03:20.025
[The Seagull]
[Invitation Exchange Voucher]

01:03:20.805 --> 01:03:23.515
This is for today, too?

01:03:36.212 --> 01:03:39.012
Yeah, thank you.

01:03:53.580 --> 01:03:57.964
Thank you to everyone for visiting
Meru Arts Center today.

01:03:57.964 --> 01:04:00.029
The performance will begin shortly.

01:04:00.029 --> 01:04:01.359
- Hey.
- Oh.

01:04:01.359 --> 01:04:03.646
You seem more nervous than usual today.

01:04:03.646 --> 01:04:05.436
- Waiting for someone?
- No.

01:04:05.436 --> 01:04:07.103
Just a friend.

01:04:07.103 --> 01:04:08.838
- A friend?
- Yeah.

01:04:08.838 --> 01:04:11.310
Food and beverages, including water,

01:04:11.310 --> 01:04:13.937
are not permitted inside the theater.

01:04:13.937 --> 01:04:16.797
For everyone's comfort,

01:04:16.797 --> 01:04:21.811
please turn off your cell phones
and all electronic devices.

01:04:21.811 --> 01:04:25.091
You're welcome to take photos
during the curtain call

01:04:25.091 --> 01:04:28.617
after the performance has ended.

01:04:34.685 --> 01:04:36.123
I really came

01:04:36.123 --> 01:04:38.709
all the way here.

01:04:38.709 --> 01:04:40.743
A mountain is a mountain,

01:04:40.743 --> 01:04:43.256
water is water,

01:04:43.256 --> 01:04:45.676
and I...

01:04:46.270 --> 01:04:49.049
I'm just the worker.

01:05:10.465 --> 01:05:11.925
Catch me if you can!

01:05:11.925 --> 01:05:14.181
- Be careful!
- No!

01:06:44.812 --> 01:06:47.558
Hello.

01:06:47.558 --> 01:06:51.931
I'm Lee Ui Yeong. I called earlier.

01:06:53.568 --> 01:06:55.955
Excuse me?

01:06:57.895 --> 01:07:00.548
Sir?

01:07:09.996 --> 01:07:12.357
Sir.

01:07:18.275 --> 01:07:20.695
Sir?

01:07:23.257 --> 01:07:24.421
Sir...

01:07:24.421 --> 01:07:26.527
Oh my!

01:07:26.527 --> 01:07:29.287
Oh my gosh, I'm so sorry.

01:07:31.381 --> 01:07:32.686
So sorry.

01:07:32.686 --> 01:07:35.139
My phone...

01:07:38.124 --> 01:07:40.291
Mr. Tae Seop?

01:07:40.291 --> 01:07:43.024
What are you doing here?

01:07:45.455 --> 01:07:46.989
Ms. Ui Yeong?

01:07:46.989 --> 01:07:48.526
Did you come to see me?

01:07:48.526 --> 01:07:50.399
What? Me?

01:07:50.399 --> 01:07:53.389
No, no. I'm here for work.

01:07:55.427 --> 01:07:58.153
Don't tell me... you're...

01:07:58.153 --> 01:08:00.870
- I'm the CEO of HOME.
- Oh, you are.

01:08:00.870 --> 01:08:03.167
So you're the CEO of HOME...

01:08:03.167 --> 01:08:05.196
What?

01:08:17.860 --> 01:08:21.729
[A one-percent chance?]
[An opportunity is still an opportunity.]

01:08:21.729 --> 01:08:25.026
[Today's to-do: Blind date]
[Tomorrow's to-do: Blind date]

01:08:25.026 --> 01:08:28.483
[I guess this is where our story ends.]

01:08:28.483 --> 01:08:32.256
[Ms. Ui Yeong]
[Ms. Seoltang]

01:08:35.377 --> 01:08:38.837
[I just didn't want to be
completely fake with you.]

01:08:45.332 --> 01:08:46.795
Why are you here?

01:08:46.795 --> 01:08:48.080
Oh, a shooting star!

01:08:48.080 --> 01:08:49.552
Hurry. Make a wish.

01:08:49.552 --> 01:08:53.554
If Ms. Ui Yeong's okay with it,
let's have her stay the night.

01:08:54.279 --> 01:08:57.233
I kept waiting, thinking maybe you'd show up.

01:08:57.233 --> 01:08:58.276
How about tomorrow night?

01:08:58.276 --> 01:09:00.908
- Ms. Ui Yeong.
- Oh...

01:09:00.908 --> 01:09:03.133
It's a basketball comic, so how about a game?

01:09:03.133 --> 01:09:05.594
If I win...

01:09:05.594 --> 01:09:08.077
You didn't come to apologize. So tell me.

01:09:08.077 --> 01:09:09.265
It's pouring outside!

01:09:09.265 --> 01:09:10.601
Ms. Ui Yeong!

01:09:10.601 --> 01:09:12.506
How do you want me

01:09:12.506 --> 01:09:15.705
to remember you?